<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Original Research</div>
    <h1>Republic Services (RSG)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Compiled by Gemini 3.1. A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Republic Services. One final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {meta.published}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(revData[revData.length - 1] / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(currentFcf / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${epsData[epsData.length - 1].toFixed(2)}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{marginHistory[marginHistory.length - 1].operating}%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to find the intrinsic value of RSG. This method values the company based on the present value of its future free cash flows.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Base Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>We start with Republic Services' most recent Free Cash Flow of <strong>${currentFcf.toLocaleString()} million</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for the next 5 years, derived from its historical compound annual growth rate.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong> using the Gordon Growth Model to capture the terminal value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>We discount all future cash flows back to today using a <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}% discount rate</strong>. This is derived from the 10-year Treasury yield of 4.18% plus a 4.00% equity risk premium reflecting RSG's stable, utility-like profile.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived mathematically from the historical 4-year Free Cash Flow CAGR. We cap extreme outliers to maintain a realistic and conservative growth projection.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Based on a current 10Y Treasury yield of 4.18% plus a 4.00% equity risk premium. Waste management is a highly resilient, recession-resistant industry with predictable cash flows, justifying a moderately lower required return.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        A 3.0% perpetual growth rate aligns with long-term GDP growth and inflation, reflecting Republic Services' pricing power and essential nature of its business.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (Current)</td>
          <td>${currentFcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
